  "commentary": "With SPX at 7096.94 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 7115 (-3689.1M) and the massive positive gamma wall at 7100 (+5012.5M), dealers are caught in a critical zone where they're likely buying this dip aggressively as part of their long gamma hedging. The PIN regime combined with the wall_break event suggests dealers will continue purchasing into weakness here, but any bounce toward 7115-7150 will face heavy dealer selling pressure from the stacked positive gamma walls above. Watch 7100 as the key support level where dealer buying should intensify, while 7115 and 7150 represent major resistance zones where dealers will lean into any rallies.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce from current levels with heavy resistance on any move back toward 7150.",
